rules.ruleString: Must be enrolled in course version {3445, 3892, M20021}

unitName: Paramedic management of maternal and neonatal health
description: This unit continues to develop the role of the paramedic as a clinician by developing knowledge and skills needed to care for birthing women and neonates in the community. The unit will be case based, and will include clinical skills laboratories and simulation to develop essential clinical skills, clinical problem solving and decision making competencies.
faculty: Faculty of Medicine, Nursing and Health Sciences
